    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-16T21:16:22+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-16T21:16:22+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T11:46:22Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-16T11:46:22Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred over the Tasman Sea extends a ridge over eastern parts of SA. A low pressure system south of the Bight will remain slow-moving until later Thursday when it will move southeastwards. An associated cold front will move across SA during Wednesday followed by a second front later Thursday and Friday. A high pressure system will move across from the west over the weekend.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW003" description="Kangaroo Island" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-16T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Medium chance of showers. Winds northerly 20 to 30 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain, most likely from the late morning. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds northerly 25 to 35 km/h tending northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm in the west in the morning. Winds north to northwesterly 25 to 40 km/h turning westerly 20 to 30 km/h in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 10 with daytime temperatures reaching around 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers. Winds west to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h tending south to southwesterly during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 13 and 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Winds southerly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching around 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
